hotspot.title: Welcome
hotspot.description: Nazareth Catholic Community is a place of welcome, connecting faith, family and education. Inspired by Jesus of Nazareth and our patrons we are people of justice each committed to building community, nourishing family life and making the world a better place.

hotspot.title: Reception
hotspot.description: Our Flinders Park campus welcomes Years 7 - 12 students from the College and their families as well as our wider community engagement programs.

hotspot.title: Drop Down Curtain
hotspot.description: Drop down curtain to separate classes and physical education learning spaces allowing for different sports to be played at the same time

hotspot.title: Sports Program
hotspot.description: Over 600 students compete for our College, with over 60 teams representing girls and boys summer and winter competitions. Opportunities also exist for participation in carnival, knockout competitions and other events. Our outstanding results speak for themselves and have significantly contributed to raising our college profile.

hotspot.title: Indoor and Outdoor Courts
hotspot.description: Indoor and outdoor basketball and netball courts, badminton and volleyball courts

hotspot.title: Skill Focus
hotspot.description: Academies to develop skills in AFLW, netball, basketball and soccer with specialist coaches and access to intercol competitions

hotspot.title: EFM Gym
hotspot.description: Access to EFM gym for training and conducting fitness testing.

hotspot.title: Oval
hotspot.description: Vast oval space to allow for all outdoor team sports to be played

hotspot.title: Cafe
hotspot.description: Creating a faith filled community of welcome and connection is a key part of our mission to nurture family life. Our community cafe’s on both sites are vibrant community hubs for families and community members to connect, meet or just relax with a great coffee and delicious snack or meal.

hotspot.title: Student Opportunities
hotspot.description: Barista training is available for Year 12 Students, providing the experience needed for future part time employment. Opportunities are provided for our Inclusive Education students, who regularly cook decadent biscuits to sell in the cafe.

hotspot.title: Open to...
hotspot.description: Open to, Years 10 - 12 students, parents, friends, staff and members of our Community.

hotspot.title: Caritas Downstairs
hotspot.description: The Caritas building allows us to cater for a wide range of learning styles in a contemporary, state of the art facility complete with seamless AV integration to support portable learning.

hotspot.title: Flexible Learning Spaces
hotspot.description: The flexible learning spaces create an adult learning environment to complement the transition of senior students into tertiary education, whilst allowing teaching staff the ability to create and present varied and diverse learning instructions to accommodate student need.

hotspot.title: Kitchenettes
hotspot.description: Kitchenettes scattered throughout the building assist senior students in self-directed learning and breaks and communal conversation

hotspot.title: Flexibility
hotspot.description: Flexibility allows for large group and year level or house gatherings

hotspot.title: Sense of Space
hotspot.description: The wide use of glass sliding doors, and floor to ceiling windows creates vision and a sense of space, and an abundance of natural light and welcoming environment

hotspot.title: Expressive Arts
hotspot.description: The expressive arts course engages students’ cognition, imagination, senses and emotions in conceptual and practical ways and involves them thinking kinaesthetically, critically and creatively. Students learn to understand, appreciate and critique the arts by making their own artworks. They also develop their ability to work collaboratively and creatively by devising, rehearsing and performing artworks.

hotspot.title: Versatile Large Space
hotspot.description: Versatile large space which acts as a classroom for Dance and Drama students as well as a theatre for Dance, Drama and Music performances.

hotspot.title: Studio Features
hotspot.description: Equipped with a sprung floor, tarquette, mirrors and black theatre curtains, which allow the space to be reconfigured for multiple purposes. Recently updated audio-visual equipment, including sound system, theatre lighting and industry standard lighting control systems.

hotspot.title: Performing Arts Space
hotspot.description: The Performing Arts Space (PAS) is used to stage a number of performances throughout the year, including Dance, Drama and Music events.

hotspot.title: Special Events
hotspot.description: This flexible space also accommodates a range of guest speakers, presentations, workshops, assemblies and other special events

hotspot.title: Veritas Centre
hotspot.description: Year 7 to 12 classes use the various areas in a flexible way for their research and reading needs. It is regularly used as a learning space for group work, study support with staff members, and a quiet space to study, read or browse our magazines and novels.

hotspot.title: Library
hotspot.description: The library is a communal space used well by students across all year levels where they may choose to either work independently, with a teacher or their peers.

hotspot.title: Student Focus
hotspot.description: A middle school focus on developing students’ note-making and paraphrasing skills, along with correct referencing and bibliography writing has been a focus as students move into their senior years of schooling. In the senior years a greater emphasis has been placed on accessing various online educational resource databases to promote greater depth of academic research.

hotspot.title: Design & Technology
hotspot.description: Students can develop a broad range of skills and knowledge exploring a range of materials such as wood and metal, in addition to exposure to system concepts such as Computer Aided Design (CAD) and Advanced Manufacturing, Product Design, hydraulic devices and interface components including programmable control devices.

hotspot.title: Specialty Areas
hotspot.description: The area comprises of 3 main specialty areas. These are: Woodwork, Metalwork and advanced manufacturing, which includes 3D Printers, a Laser Cutter & Vinyl Cutter. Students use Autodesk Fusion 360 to design projects for manufacturing in a variety of materials.

hotspot.title: Pedal Prix
hotspot.description: Pedal Prix is also offered as a co-curricular sport, that the Design & Technology Faculty run.

hotspot.title: Arts Program
hotspot.description: Opportunities to experience and develop skills with a range of different materials and techniques, including drawing, painting, printmaking, sculpture, mixed media, graphic design and product design. We have a dedicated clay area and kiln for firing ceramic works.

hotspot.title: Software Access
hotspot.description: Student access to Adobe Suite allows Arts students to work with industry-standard software and explore new media.

hotspot.title: Annual Art Exhibition
hotspot.description: Workshops and curriculum extension with professional artists and Annual Art Exhibition. Other opportunities for students to showcase their art work occur throughout the year. .

hotspot.title: Partnership between home and school
hotspot.description: A strong partnership between home and school is the key to success so we are a community that is committed to strengthening families’ engagement in their children’s learning and wellbeing.

hotspot.title: Enrichment Activities
hotspot.description: Students at Nazareth have the opportunity to participate in enrichment activities spanning a variety of disciplines as well as camps and retreats as part of College life.

hotspot.title: Student Leadership Program
hotspot.description: The Student leadership program at Nazareth provides opportunities for students to engage with the school community s well as the wider community. A wide range of leadership opportunities are available for students, with both elected positions and voluntary positions.

hotspot.title: Five Habits of Excellence
hotspot.description: At Nazareth, we have adopted the Nazareth Five Habits of Excellence as a ‘roadmap’ to success.

hotspot.title: Social Justice Principles
hotspot.description: We are committed to the social justice principles of the Church, and, as stated in our Mission, are inspired by Jesus of Nazareth and our Patrons... each committed to building community, nourishing family life and making the world a better place. Nazareth Outreach Projects (NOW) are an extension of our values and are supported by the entire community. We have an extensive array of projects we currently support. Our projects extend beyond Australia, with projects internationally, nationally as well as a local level.

hotspot.title: House System
hotspot.description: Nazareth has a house system for students that aims to create a sense of connection, belonging and identity for each student in a small group within the College. It is also to foster school ‘spirit’ through having fun. Each house is divided into vertically grouped Mentor classes

hotspot.title: TEF Facilities
hotspot.description: TEF facilities feature modern food preparation and cooking facilities in the domestic kitchen. Students have access to a shared kitchenette space, which is equipped with tools and equipment to construct basic and extravagant dishes of food.

hotspot.title: Technology and Food
hotspot.description: Technology and Food subjects build life skills for life long learners. This occurs through the knowledge and practical skill development within the topics of food preparation and cooking, nutrition and health, sustainable practices within the home involving food and textiles items, and diversity of food choice within our society.

hotspot.title: Career Paths
hotspot.description: Technology and food subjects in the SACE may lead students into a range of future career paths or interests, including Nutrition, Food and Hospitality, Child Studies, Design Technologies

hotspot.title: Commercial Kitchen
hotspot.description: A commercial kitchen with restaurant based cookers, ovens, salamander and food service ware offers our students the opportunity to learn in a real commercial kitchen workspace.

hotspot.title: Textiles Room
hotspot.description: The Textiles room features 22 sewing machines and overlockers which enable students to sew and construct fabric items to a commercial standard, along with resources to support creative design in textiles and the development of educational toys and games for children for SACE Child studies.

hotspot.title: Digital Technologies Area Upstairs
hotspot.description: · Wireless 1080p projectors with sound systems for presentations, group collaboration and student work · Photo quality printers for high quality printing · Desktop computers and screens for ‘high end’ applications · Raspberry Pi mini computers to explore different operating systems · Breakout space for group collaboration · 3d printing for prototyping and developing complete digital solutions · Open layout encourages group collaboration and teamwork.

hotspot.title: Music Program
hotspot.description: Our Music programs at Nazareth aim to provide music education of the highest quality. With a balance of traditional musical concepts and innovative musical experience, we instill in our students the relevance of music education in our society. Our purpose built Music Centre enables students the opportunity to study both Music and Music Technology. A keyboard and music technology lab, large band room, recording studio facility, and instrumental rooms enables students to excel.

hotspot.title: Practice Rooms
hotspot.description: Instrumental practice rooms for private tuition or student practice and secure instrumental store room for students to safely leave their instruments whilst at school

hotspot.title: Recording Studio
hotspot.description: Dedicated recording studio for isolated recording of vocals and instruments

hotspot.title: Band Room
hotspot.description: Acoustically treated band room for ensemble rehearsing catering for a wide variety of styles including rock bands, jazz big bands, choirs, vocal ensembles, percussion groups, concert bands and more

hotspot.title: Concert Grand Piano
hotspot.description: Professional standard concert grand piano for pianists to practice and perform on

hotspot.title: Music Tech
hotspot.description: Purpose-built music technology facilities, with industry standard digital audio workstations for students to record, create and compose
